{
  "texts": [
    "Some GR methods like CorpusLM [152] have experimented with a decoder-only structure of the LLM Llama2 [286], requiring more training computational power but not significantly improving performance.",
    "Research is needed to determine which structure is more suitable for generative retrieval.",
    "Additionally, whether increasing model and data size could lead to emergent phenomena similar to those observed in LLMs [244,312] is also a promising research direction.6.1.2 Handling Dynamic Corpora.",
    "Real-world applications often involve dynamically changing corpora, such as the web and news archives, where incremental learning is essential.",
    "However, for language models, indexing new documents inevitably leads to forgetting old ones, posing a challenge for GR systems."
  ]
}